The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili, Chronicle Reporter THIEVES last night broke into Bulawayo Mayor councillor Solomon Mguni’s car and stole cash among other valuables at his home in Nkulumane suburb. Cllr Mguni discovered the crime on Thursday morning. He said he had forgotten his wallet in the vehicle and the thieves also got away with his car battery. Nkulumane suburb is one of the six western suburbs that police identified as hotspots for burglary cases which in some instances lead to women being raped. More details to follow…